<br>
Onebadmutha, a deserter from the Freeport militia woke up from his lazy slumber out of the West Freeport gutter, to the noise of yelling. It was Jigglypimpf, the first season druid, who spent the days shouting &quot;sow and port for donations&quot;, and promptly hiding after receiving coin from gullible adventurers.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's been proclaimed by the citizens of Norrath that Sunday, April 1 is to be Beggar Appreciation Day, a day of gift-giving to take place at the Freeport Arena,&quot; Jigglypimpf exclaimed to the unkempt legion whose ranks seemed to grow with every tenday. &quot;They must have finally realized how important we are to their travels. For without us, who could they give away that heavy coin and hard earned loot to? Come, let us get bound at the Freeport arena so we can receive the bounty that we so richly deserve.&quot; Onebadmutha polished his family begging cup with this newbie tunic. &quot;Today I shall earn a Wurmslayer. To the Arena!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
Date: Sunday April 1<br>
Place: West Freeport Arena<br>
Time: 5 PM EST<br>
<br>
The Warlords of Steel has gathered Antonica's most infamous beggars at the Freeport Arena. All players are invited to the First Bertoxxulous Beggar Bash. For a mere 2 pp, you can show your favorite beggars how you feel about them. Those of you who cannot make it but still wish to attend (including citizens from other servers), please create Freeport resident and make your way to the Arena ahead of time to participate as a beggar.<br>
<br>
100 pp cash prizes will be awarded to the best beggar name, best beggar actor, funniest beggar, the most creative beggar basher, and biggest overkiller.<br>
<br>
